 Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Ridel had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Agnes heiress of Perigord."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1062–Female":"1062–Surnud","1075–1120":"1075–1120","–Female":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1120":"1120","1075":"1075","1062":"1062","about 1075":"umbes 1075","Stamford, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1062–Female":"1062–Kuollut","1075–1120":"1075–1120","–Female":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1120":"1120","1075":"1075","1062":"1062","about 1075":"noin 1075","Stamford, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–":"Décédé","1062–Female":"1062–Décédée","1075–1120":"1075–1120","–Female":"Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1120":"1120","1075":"1075","1062":"1062","about 1075":"environ 1075","Stamford, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert Ridel a eu au moins 2 fils et 1 fille avec Agnes heiress of Perigord."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1062–Female":"1062–Verstorben","1075–1120":"1075–1120","–Female":"Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1120":"1120","1075":"1075","1062":"1062","about 1075":"um 1075","Stamford, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Robert Ridel hatte mit Agnes heiress of Perigord mindestens 2 Söhne und 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","1062–Female":"1062